{
  "stem": "7546.1",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And then when the war broke out, he wore a band with a swastika, and I had to hide because I wasn't the nicest kid in the class.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So I hid, he shouldn't see me.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, music wasn't one of my best subjects.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, yes.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I was very avid reader.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I read almost anything I could get my-- my hands on.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I did read in the '30s-- I knew already how to read in 1933-- especially I read about '32 or '33 that the [INAUDIBLE] was burning, then that a man called Adolf Hitler is coming to power.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And then the leader of Germany by the name of Hindenburg died, which gave Hitler the power to become the chief of Germany.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And the first thing that I read was that he immediately built a camp, a concentration camp, which was the first one that I heard of, was Dachau.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But somehow or other, the [INAUDIBLE] of science and music simply couldn't build concentration camp where they're taking Jews for no good reason at all simply because they're Jews.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So I sort of figured that either the Polish papers is sort of putting a little bit of [INAUDIBLE] on it, or maybe the Jewish paper is putting a little bit [INAUDIBLE] on it.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I didn't believe that such things are happening until 1938 November, during the Kristallnacht.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Now, everybody is under the impression that Kristallnacht-- crystal night, the night of the broken crystal-- happened in Germany.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Well, 99% probably happened in Germany.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "In Lodz where I was born, there was a crystal store by the name of L.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Winters, beautiful store.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And on the main drag of Lodz called [POLISH].",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And there was a store called L.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
